## Limitations

This report is limited by the availability of recent data and the complexity of isolating mental health as a singular factor in criminal behavior. The relationship between mental health and crime is influenced by numerous variables, including socioeconomic factors, substance abuse, and the availability of mental health services. Further research is needed to explore these interactions in greater depth.

